# Create a new User

> This endpoint creates a new `User` associating it with the provided email address.

## OpenAPI

````yaml https://api.gnosispay.com/api-docs/spec.json post /api/v1/auth/signup
paths:
  path: /api/v1/auth/signup
  method: post
  servers:
    - url: https://api.gnosispay.com
  request:
    security:
      - title: bearerAuth
        parameters:
          query: {}
          header:
            Authorization:
              type: http
              scheme: bearer
          cookie: {}
    parameters:
      path: {}
      query: {}
      header: {}
      cookie: {}
    body:
      application/json:
        schemaArray:
          - type: object
            properties:
              authEmail:
                allOf:
                  - type: string
                    format: email
                    description: Email address for the new user
              otp:
                allOf:
                  - type: string
                    minLength: 6
                    maxLength: 6
                    description: >-
                      One-time password for email verification (optional during
                      transition period)
              referralCouponCode:
                allOf:
                  - type: string
                    description: Referral coupon code for the new user
              marketingCampaign:
                allOf:
                  - type: string
                    description: Marketing campaign identifier
              partnerId:
                allOf:
                  - type: string
                    description: Optional ID of the partner that referred the user
            required: true
            requiredProperties:
              - authEmail
        examples:
          example:
            value:
              authEmail: jsmith@example.com
              otp: <string>
              referralCouponCode: <string>
              marketingCampaign: <string>
              partnerId: <string>
  response:
    '201':
      application/json:
        schemaArray:
          - type: object
            properties:
              id:
                allOf:
                  - type: string
                    description: Unique identifier of the created user
              token:
                allOf:
                  - type: string
                    description: JWT token for authentication
              hasSignedUp:
                allOf:
                  - type: boolean
                    description: Indicates if the user has completed signup
            requiredProperties:
              - id
              - token
              - hasSignedUp
        examples:
          example:
            value:
              id: <string>
              token: <string>
              hasSignedUp: true
        description: User was created successfully
    '400':
      application/json:
        schemaArray:
          - type: object
            properties:
              error:
                allOf:
                  - type: string
                    example: Invalid partner ID
        examples:
          example:
            value:
              error: Invalid partner ID
        description: Invalid partner ID
    '401':
      application/json:
        schemaArray:
          - type: object
            properties:
              error:
                allOf:
                  - type: string
                    example: Invalid or expired OTP
        examples:
          example:
            value:
              error: Invalid or expired OTP
        description: Invalid or expired OTP
    '409':
      application/json:
        schemaArray:
          - type: object
            properties:
              error:
                allOf:
                  - type: string
                    example: >-
                      Email address already registered or Wallet address already
                      associated with another account
        examples:
          example:
            value:
              error: >-
                Email address already registered or Wallet address already
                associated with another account
        description: Email address or wallet address already registered
    '422':
      application/json:
        schemaArray:
          - type: object
            properties:
              error:
                allOf:
                  - type: string
                    example: Invalid email format
        examples:
          example:
            value:
              error: Invalid email format
        description: Invalid request body
    '500':
      application/json:
        schemaArray:
          - type: object
            properties:
              error:
                allOf:
                  - type: string
                    description: Details about the server error
                    example: An unexpected error occurred
        examples:
          example:
            value:
              error: An unexpected error occurred
        description: Internal server error
  deprecated: false
  type: path
components:
  schemas: {}

````

